item.title: Help Please.!
item.dc:creator: @D_R_U_G D R U G
item.description:
@D_R_U_G wrote:

you can download JDK 6.0 update 10 then find the path

How To Find The Path,

My Computer-
Local Disk(C:)-
Program Files-
Java-
jdk1.6.0_10(or what ever jdk you have, as long as you got a javac.exe in the bin folder)-
bin-

then add javac.exe at the end so it should look like this-

C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_10\bin\javac.exe

Also you can use this, just add it to your compiler-NOTE YOU NEED JDK 6 UPDATE 10

@ECHO OFF
TITLE Mod Jason Compiler
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_10\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
pause
